e the harbor's tides and currents and to show how they influence geological processes and pollution susceptibility. Storm surge measurements going back to the early 1990s document some of the extreme high waters experienced, and descriptions of some of the more interesting or important marine species of plants and animals found in the harbor are also included. The book discusses the century-long conflicts that local residents have fought in order to preserve this beautiful place, and it documents the tools that currently exist to help manage the harbor well into the twenty-first century. An excellent supplement to any high school or undergraduate environmental course, Between Stony Brook Harbor Tides provides readers with a basis for embracing the significance of the harbor and what it can bring to future residents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCoastal ecologyzNew York (State)zStony Brook. 0aCoastal ecology--New York (State)--Stony Brook. 0aCoastal zone managementzNew York (State)zStony Brook. 0aHarborszNew York (State)zStony Brook. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Ecology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Marine Biology. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Society. 7aSCIENCE / Environmental Science (see also Chemistry / Environmental).2bisacsh1 aBowman, Malcolm J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2017z978311149102840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846235640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462356/original  a978-3-11-149102-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles